<TITLE> Aug 21 accused to be grilled again: IO </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 20 (bdnews24.com)  The accused in the Aug 21 2004 grenade attack cases will be remanded for interrogations again, the present investigation officer in the cases said on Thursday. "We will petition the court to place the accused on remand again soon," IO Abdul Kahar Akhand told bdnews24.com. "In addition to grilling 14 accused in the case, efforts will be made to bring two brothers Mottakin and Morshalin, back to Bangladesh after their arrests in India." "There is evidence of their involvement in the grenade attack." CID senior assistant superintendent of police Akhand was appointed on Aug 13 as further investigation into the grenade attack was ordered. bdnew
